HEADWORD: Intertexture
<hw>In`ter*tex"ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act
of interweaving, or the state of being interwoven; that which is
interwoven.</def> ⟦rdquo⟧Knit in nice <xex>intertexture</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Skirted thick with <qex>intertexture</qex> firm⟦br⟧
Of thorny boughs.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

